<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="312" pageId="9" pageNumber="310" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1660,2009]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,432]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="311" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1912,1937]" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Description.</emphasis>
Adult. Colour. Conspicuous sexual dimorphism. Male (
<figureCitation box="[1010,1097,1912,1937]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24. Craspedolepta merzi sp. nov. adult. 16. Habitus, male, lateral view. 17. Habitus, female, lateral view. 18. Antenna. 19. Antennal segments 9 and 10. 20. Head. 21. Male forewing. 22. Female forewing. 23. Female terminalia, lateral view. 24. Male terminalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1039112/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) almost entirely black, dirty yellow or ochreous laterally. Antenna white to yellow; segments 9 and 10 brown. Eyes yellow to brown; ocelli orange to brown. Tip of labium black. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[741,827,1984,2009]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24. Craspedolepta merzi sp. nov. adult. 16. Habitus, male, lateral view. 17. Habitus, female, lateral view. 18. Antenna. 19. Antennal segments 9 and 10. 20. Head. 21. Male forewing. 22. Female forewing. 23. Female terminalia, lateral view. 24. Male terminalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1039112/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="310">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) with transparent membrane and brown veins; with scattered brown spots of uniform size, absent or very scarce in basal half, more numerous and slightly denser in apical half. Hindwing whitish. Legs pale yellow. Abdomen dark brown with pale yellow margins of sclerites. Terminalia dark brown, subgenital plate light brown basally. Younger specimens with more expanded light colour, sometimes with darker longitudinal stripes visible on dorsum of mesothorax. Female (
<figureCitation box="[1150,1233,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24. Craspedolepta merzi sp. nov. adult. 16. Habitus, male, lateral view. 17. Habitus, female, lateral view. 18. Antenna. 19. Antennal segments 9 and 10. 20. Head. 21. Male forewing. 22. Female forewing. 23. Female terminalia, lateral view. 24. Male terminalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1039112/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) similar but with more extended yellow ochreous patches on head and thorax. Pronotum yellow with four brown dots, mesopraescutum yellow with two brown patches, mesoscutum with six longitudinal brown stripes. Forewing (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[313,1277,486,1904]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 16 ‒ 24. Craspedolepta merzi sp. nov. adult. 16. Habitus, male, lateral view. 17. Habitus, female, lateral view. 18. Antenna. 19. Antennal segments 9 and 10. 20. Head. 21. Male forewing. 22. Female forewing. 23. Female terminalia, lateral view. 24. Male terminalia, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1039112/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="311">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) with scattered brown spots in apical two thirds; few to no spots in cells c+sc, r1 and cu2. Terminalia ochreous with brown patches. Younger specimens with more expanded light colour.
</paragraph>
